> Here's a behavior of M2 that I find suboptimal. I'd like to
> promote a module (with relations) to a larger ring, where
> the variable names match, as follows, but I have to form
> a presentation matrix, promote that, and then take the coker
> instead. Is there a better way? Why NOT make "substitute" do
> this, or if not, then **?
> 
> Regards,
> 
> David
> 
> kk = ZZ/101
> R1=kk[x]
> M=R1^1/x^2
> R2=kk[x,y]
> substitute(M, R2) -- produces an error suggesting the next line
> R2**M -- also produces an error!
